# WORKFLOW RULES

### Rule 3: Agents Involved Footer
Every response MUST end with "Agents involved: [agent names]" or "Agents involved: None (direct tool usage)".

### Rule 32: Bug Validation
Bug validation requests -> route to bug-validator subagent. READ-ONLY: validate against Confluence first, then codebase. Report to `Cursor-Project/reports/YYYY-MM-DD/BugValidation_*.md`. Follow `.cursor/commands/bug-validate.md`.

### Rule 33: Database Queries
Database queries -> use correct PostgreSQL MCP server for the requested environment. See database_workflow.mdc for connection details and query patterns.

### Rule 35: Test Case Generation
Test case requests -> run cross-dependency-finder FIRST, then pass output as cross_dependency_data to test-case-generator. Follow `.cursor/commands/test-case-generate.md`.

### Rule 35a: Cross-Dependency Merge Workflow
When user provides a Jira key: (1) look up merge history for that key in local git and GitLab; (2) if merge exists, sync that branch; (3) include technical_details in output. Follow `.cursor/commands/cross-dependency-finder.md`.

### Rule 36: Run Playwright Tests
Run Playwright tests -> energo-ts-run subagent, cursor branch only (Rule ENERGOTS.0). Follow `.cursor/commands/energo-ts-run.md`.

### Rule 37: HandsOff Flow
Jira ticket + /HandsOff -> full pipeline via hands-off subagent. Follow `.cursor/commands/hands-off.md`. See handsoff_playwright_report.mdc for lessons learned.
